Congratulations!   You are definitely on the right track to pain relief and feeling better because you are looking for a Certified Rolfer.

Hello, my name is James Donatelli and I am a Chronic Pain and Athletic Performance Specialist. Throughout my decade of experience as a Certified Rolfer, I have witnessed the transformational power of Rolfing in countless individuals who were suffering from persistent pain that hindered their daily activities and enjoyment of life.

In my wellness center which is now located in Hypoluxo, Florida, I have had the privilege of working with a diverse range of clients, including athletes, active individuals, and those who simply want to lead a pain-free and vibrant life. No matter your background or the pain experienced, I believe that everyone deserves the opportunity to live their life to the fullest. As a specialist in chronic pain management, my primary goal is to help my clients alleviate their pain and regain their freedom of movement. As a performance specialist, my next goal is then to help your body perform at an even higher level to meet today's ever increasing demands from family, work and activities. 

For athletes, I understand the importance of optimal performance and recovery. Whether you are a tennis, baseball or soccer player, or any other kind of athlete that involves physical effort and precise movements, I can provide specialized assistance tailored to your specific needs. I am experienced in treating sports-related injuries, improving athletic performance, and helping high-achievers who care about performance up their game and get back on track as quickly as possible.

However, Rolfing is not exclusively for athletes, it simply takes a clear decision and a strong commitment to the program to get better. Many individuals who have been enduring pain for months or even years have found relief through my Rolfing program which is an enhanced 12-session program that combines Rolfing, Cranial Sacral Therapy, Rolf Movement Education, cross-training, nutrition coaching (upon request), and cutting-edge electronic therapies like PEMF or laser treatments (when necessary). I believe in a comprehensive holistic approach to healing, addressing not only the physical aspects of the pain but also the emotional and energetic components as well. This program is custom tailored to address your specific needs and to ensure that you receive safe, effective, and long-lasting results.

My commitment to all my clients' well-being extends beyond the treatment sessions. I prioritize education and empowerment, equipping my clients with the knowledge and tools they need to continue their progress independently. Whether you are an athlete striving for peak performance or an individual seeking to enhance your energy and overall quality of life, I am dedicated to helping you achieve your goals.

Choosing the right Certified Rolfer is crucial, as it requires trust and a personal connection. If my approach resonates with you and aligns with your needs and aspirations, I invite you to schedule a consultation. Together, we can embark on a journey towards a pain-free and vibrant life.

In conclusion, as a Certified Rolfer specializing in chronic pain and athletic performance, I am committed to helping my clients overcome pain, improve their energy levels, and enhance their quality of life. From professional athletes to individuals seeking relief from long-standing pain, I offer a tailor-made 12-session program that combine various techniques and therapies for effective and lasting results. If you are in search of a health provider who can guide you towards a pain-free and vibrant life, I encourage you to fill out the goals and outcomes questionnaire on my website so we can then discuss your specific goals and needs and how my program can serve you. 

Working with me you can expect to:

  • Reduce chronic pain,
  • Improve posture, balance and flexibility,
  • Feel stronger and more grounded,
  • Reduce recovery time between workouts,
  • Reduce chronic inflammation, 
  • Slow the aging process,
  • Reduce scar tissue adhesions after injuries or surgeries (if any),
  • Straighten scoliotic curves in the spine (if any),
  • Strengthen hips, knees, feet and ankles,
  • Dramatically reduce chances of future athletic injuries. 


If this looks, sounds or feels like possible fit for you, please visit my website at  www.DonatelliWellness.com to fill out the questionnaire.  You will then get a FREE, 15-min Telephone Consultation to discuss how my custom-tailored Rolfing program can help you. 

To Your Future Health, Wealth and Performance!

Profile:

As a Certified Advanced Rolfer?, I help my clients restore their body's natural movement through structural alignment interventions and holistic bodywork. Every body is different, so the starting point, speed of transition, and outcome of the work will be unique to each client.

 

Education

· The Rolf Institute® of Structural Integration, Boulder, Colorado

· Primitive reflexive movements (embryological and early development)

· Space awareness body-mapping with SourcePoint Therapy®

· Cranial Sacral Therapy

· Diaphragmatic releasing and balancing

· Yoga, Thai Chi and Qi-Gong


After years of athletics?gymnastics, two marathons, acrobatics, dancing, lacrosse, fencing and music?I began to notice pain in my body. I found myself wanting a more balanced and individual approach to body development and awareness. In my search for sustainable health, I received the Rolfing® Ten Series and have been studying and advocating Rolfing® Structural Integration ever since.

 

When the body is out of structural balance, movement is harder and often causes excessive wear and pain. Through Rolfing® I felt as though the forces of gravity were on my side. Instead of working against my body, everyday movements became easier and pain-free. As my body slowly changed (and continues to change), my ideas about health, healing and personal growth have been transformed.

 

Along with relief from pain from a sports injury, I found a renewed sense of enjoyment in simple daily activities. I was amazed?not only had the pain subsided, but I found a calming sense of ease and grace in my movements. I want to help you find the same.

Bethany Ward, MBA is dual faculty at the Rolf Institute of Structural Integration in the Rolfing and Rolf Movement Integration departments. She is past-president of the Ida P. Rolf Research Foundation and was involved in the early stages of the International Fascia Research Congress and Fascia Research Society. Her articles on the practical implications of fascia research have been published in Massage and Bodywork Magazine, the Structural Integration Journal, the International Association of Structural Integration Yearbook, Massage Magazine, and Endurance magazine, among others.

Profile:

I began my practice as a Certified Rolfer in 2001. In 2009, after passing a rigorous exam, I became a Board Certified Structural Integrator. In 2019 I became a Certified Advanced Rolfer. In addition, I have taken numerous Rolf Movement Integration classes, learned Neural Mobilization - a refined method for releasing nerve restrictions; Muscle Energy Technique - a gentle, systematic way to release deep restrictions in the pelvis and spine; SourcePoint Therapy - an energetic approach to Rolfing which helps to bring order, balance, harmony and flow to my client's system and Hiroyoshi Tahata's The Art of Yield.

In 2013 I became a Somatic Experiencing Practitioner. Somatic Experiencing is the most effective way to heal nervous system dysregulation at the root of chronc stress, chronic pain and stored trauma. Through years of study with Kathy Kain and Lawrence Heller, I have gained specific skills necessary for successfully working with adolescents and adults who experienced trauma within the first three years of life, including prenatal and birth trauma.

I specialize in helping people heal from postural problems, physical injury, chronic stress, chronic pain and traumatic experiences. In addition, I have a special interest in helping to heal the trauma associated with social oppression. I primarily serve clients in Stanislaus, San Joaquin, Tuolumne and Merced Counties and occasionally see clients from the Bay Area, Fresno and Sacramento who are looking for my unique skill set. I am able to provide Rolfing sessions, non-touch/light touch sessions guided by Rolf Movement, SourcePoint Therapy and The Art of Yield, Somatic Experiencing sessions, or a blend of all of my skills appropriate to your needs.

Profile:

Dr. Boblett has 20 years of experience.  The Rolf Journal has published 9 of his articles, reflecting a strong commitment to continued research.  But his approach is practical rather than theoretical, with a strong focus on day-to-day function.  

Dr. Boblett brings time-tested strategies to foot, knee, neck, hamstring, lumbar, and shoulder dysfunction.  Though he works a great deal with triathletes, marathoners, cyclists, golfers, and yoga practitioners, he also provides specific solutions for busy professionals chained to desks, phones, and computer screens.  His tools include detailed analysis, deep hands-on work, and (if required) suggestions for "homework" that can restore movement to frozen joints and muscles.

Finally, Dr. Boblett's Advanced certification lets him customize his treatment for your specific issues.  So what are your goals?  Rehab?  Sports performance?  Optimal aging?  All three?  Let's plan!
In addition to Rolfing training, Dr. Boblett is certified as a Posture Alignment Specialist by Egoscue, giving him the full range of tools to guarantee tangible results for his clients.

    Jean Nguyen is a dedicated Certified Rolfer and Clinical Massage Therapist known for her intuitive touch and deep understanding of the mind-body connection. She graduated with honors from the Soma Institute in Chicago in 2011 and dove into deeper studies at the Rolfing Institute in Boulder, CO, graduating in 2015. From teaching massage for several years at the Soma Institute, assisting advance workshops, to volunteering as a manual therapist at numerous Chicago Marathon's, Jean has cultivated and nourished a holistic approach to bodywork.

    Jean's goal in a session is to help her clients achieve balance and relief from pain and tension.  Whether during a therapeutic massage or a Rolfing session she works to counteract dysfunctional movement patterns and promote a pain-free lifestyle.  Jean knows through experience that the first step to living with ease is to facilitate the clients body awareness and ability to overcome the day-to-day stresses placed on their bodies.  Jean's compassionate nature and commitment to ongoing learning and professional development make her a trusted and respected practioner among her clients and colleagues alike.
 

Visit www.MovementMedChicago.com for further details and booking.

Profile:

Congratulations!   You are definitely on the right track to pain relief and feeling better because you are looking for a Certified Rolfer.

Hello, my name is James Donatelli and I am a Chronic Pain and Athletic Performance Specialist. Throughout my decade of experience as a Certified Rolfer, I have witnessed the transformational power of Rolfing in countless individuals who were suffering from persistent pain that hindered their daily activities and enjoyment of life.

In my wellness center which is now located in Hypoluxo, Florida, I have had the privilege of working with a diverse range of clients, including athletes, active individuals, and those who simply want to lead a pain-free and vibrant life. No matter your background or the pain experienced, I believe that everyone deserves the opportunity to live their life to the fullest. As a specialist in chronic pain management, my primary goal is to help my clients alleviate their pain and regain their freedom of movement. As a performance specialist, my next goal is then to help your body perform at an even higher level to meet today's ever increasing demands from family, work and activities. 

For athletes, I understand the importance of optimal performance and recovery. Whether you are a tennis, baseball or soccer player, or any other kind of athlete that involves physical effort and precise movements, I can provide specialized assistance tailored to your specific needs. I am experienced in treating sports-related injuries, improving athletic performance, and helping high-achievers who care about performance up their game and get back on track as quickly as possible.

However, Rolfing is not exclusively for athletes, it simply takes a clear decision and a strong commitment to the program to get better. Many individuals who have been enduring pain for months or even years have found relief through my Rolfing program which is an enhanced 12-session program that combines Rolfing, Cranial Sacral Therapy, Rolf Movement Education, cross-training, nutrition coaching (upon request), and cutting-edge electronic therapies like PEMF or laser treatments (when necessary). I believe in a comprehensive holistic approach to healing, addressing not only the physical aspects of the pain but also the emotional and energetic components as well. This program is custom tailored to address your specific needs and to ensure that you receive safe, effective, and long-lasting results.

My commitment to all my clients' well-being extends beyond the treatment sessions. I prioritize education and empowerment, equipping my clients with the knowledge and tools they need to continue their progress independently. Whether you are an athlete striving for peak performance or an individual seeking to enhance your energy and overall quality of life, I am dedicated to helping you achieve your goals.

Choosing the right Certified Rolfer is crucial, as it requires trust and a personal connection. If my approach resonates with you and aligns with your needs and aspirations, I invite you to schedule a consultation. Together, we can embark on a journey towards a pain-free and vibrant life.

In conclusion, as a Certified Rolfer specializing in chronic pain and athletic performance, I am committed to helping my clients overcome pain, improve their energy levels, and enhance their quality of life. From professional athletes to individuals seeking relief from long-standing pain, I offer a tailor-made 12-session program that combine various techniques and therapies for effective and lasting results. If you are in search of a health provider who can guide you towards a pain-free and vibrant life, I encourage you to fill out the goals and outcomes questionnaire on my website so we can then discuss your specific goals and needs and how my program can serve you. 

Working with me you can expect to:

  • Reduce chronic pain,
  • Improve posture, balance and flexibility,
  • Feel stronger and more grounded,
  • Reduce recovery time between workouts,
  • Reduce chronic inflammation, 
  • Slow the aging process,
  • Reduce scar tissue adhesions after injuries or surgeries (if any),
  • Straighten scoliotic curves in the spine (if any),
  • Strengthen hips, knees, feet and ankles,
  • Dramatically reduce chances of future athletic injuries. 


If this looks, sounds or feels like possible fit for you, please visit my website at  www.DonatelliWellness.com to fill out the questionnaire.  You will then get a FREE, 15-min Telephone Consultation to discuss how my custom-tailored Rolfing program can help you. 

To Your Future Health, Wealth and Performance!


James J Donatelli

Profile:
Jeannine Olson, M.A., M.S. is a  Certified Advanced Rolfer?, a Rolf Movement practitioner, and a Licensed Clinical Professional Counselor.

I have worked in field of human growth and healing for the past 30 years.  My introduction to Rolfing was in 1990 and the experience convinced me that Rolfing can provide a way for profound healing, both on the physical and the emotional level.  In my practice I have found that Rolfing can relieve low back, neck or shoulder pain, breathing problems, jaw tension and TMJ.  It can restore plasticity to scars and bring mobility to injured areas.  My goal is to restore freedom of movement throughout the body.

I have worked with adults and children suffering from physical trauma, chronic pain, emotional trauma, and overuse injuries. As a way of supporting the Rolfing work, I have  also trained in Somatic Experiencing, a way of releasing trauma in the nervous system, Rolf Movement, EMDR (Eye Movement Desensitization Therapy), hypnotherapy, cranial-sacral therapy, working with nerves, and visceral manipulation.

Contact Jeannine for an appointment at 443-799-1330.

Profile:

As Certified Rolfer? Keith works in the Ten-Series model developed by Dr. Ida Rolf, which he enjoys sharing with those new to structural bodywork. He completed the certification program at the Rolf Institute in Boulder, Colorado in 2021 and recently pursued additional training and mentorship with advanced Rolf Movement instructor Rebecca Carli. Additionally, Keith has over two decades of experience as a massage therapist and has taught yoga in the Washington area since the late 90s. Throughout his career, Keith has worked with almost every body type?from professional dancers and NFL football players to novice yogis and those new to sports and movement. 

In 2002, after five extended trips to India, Keith was formally authorized to teach Ashtanga yoga by Sri K. Pattabhi Jois. He later co-founded and ran the Ashtanga Yoga Studio DC for many years before moving the studio online during the pandemic. In addition to Rolfing and online yoga classes, Keith offers private, one-on-one yoga instruction at a physical therapy clinic.

Outside the studio, Keith loves all forms of movement?from ultramarathons to rock/ice climbing to windsurfing and cycling. Recently, he has been working out with an Olympic weightlifting club and spending time with functional fitness coaches as ways to experiment with movement.

?Keith is kind and patient and encourages clients to challenge themselves. In his practice, you?ll find people of all ages and abilities surprised and delighted at what their bodies are capable of.?

CERTIFICATIONS AND LICENSURE

  • Certified Rolfer, Rolf Institute, Boulder, CO

  • Licensed Massage Therapist, Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, Baltimore, MD

  • Licensed Massage Therapist, DC Department of Health, Board of Massage Therapy, Washington, DC

  • Certified Massage Therapist, National Certification Board for Therapeutic Massage and Bodywork, McLean, VA

EDUCATION

  • Basic Rolfing Certification Program, Dr. Ida Rolf Institute, Boulder, CO

  • Shri K Pattabhi Jois Ashtanga Yoga Shala, Mysore, India

  • Massage Training Certification Program, Potomac Massage Training Institute, Washington, DC

  • BBA, University of Oklahoma, Norman, OK

EXPERIENCE

Certified Rolfer, Rolfing and Movement, Kensington, MD (2021?present). Provides Ten-Series Rolfing protocol to clients of all skills and backgrounds. Particular experience working with runners, dancers, and yogis. Provides bodywork backstage at the Kennedy Center to the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater.

Owner and Lead Instructor, Ashtanga Yoga Studio, Washington, DC (2012?present). Teaches Mysore-style and led classes to students of all levels. Offers one-on-one instruction and therapeutic massage to students interested in deepening their practice. Manages the studio and co-presents workshops on topics ranging from breath and mindfulness to joint health.

Ashtanga Yoga Instructor, Restore Motion, Rockville, MD (2022?present). Works one-on-one with clients and coordinates with staff physical therapists to support clients? movement goals and to enhance strength, flexibility, and body awareness.

Ashtanga Yoga Instructor, Ashtanga Yoga Center, Washington, DC (1999-2012). Taught Mysore and led classes to students of all levels. Taught anatomy for the studio?s 200-hour teacher training program.

Certified Massage Therapist, Self-Employed, Washington, DC (1999?2012). Offered therapeutic massage to a variety of clients ranging from serious athletes to weekend warriors.

Profile:

Congratulations!   You are definitely on the right track to pain relief and feeling better because you are looking for a Certified Rolfer.

Hello, my name is James Donatelli and I am a Chronic Pain and Athletic Performance Specialist. Throughout my decade of experience as a Certified Rolfer, I have witnessed the transformational power of Rolfing in countless individuals who were suffering from persistent pain that hindered their daily activities and enjoyment of life.

In my wellness center which is now located in Hypoluxo, Florida, I have had the privilege of working with a diverse range of clients, including athletes, active individuals, and those who simply want to lead a pain-free and vibrant life. No matter your background or the pain experienced, I believe that everyone deserves the opportunity to live their life to the fullest. As a specialist in chronic pain management, my primary goal is to help my clients alleviate their pain and regain their freedom of movement. As a performance specialist, my next goal is then to help your body perform at an even higher level to meet today's ever increasing demands from family, work and activities. 

For athletes, I understand the importance of optimal performance and recovery. Whether you are a tennis, baseball or soccer player, or any other kind of athlete that involves physical effort and precise movements, I can provide specialized assistance tailored to your specific needs. I am experienced in treating sports-related injuries, improving athletic performance, and helping high-achievers who care about performance up their game and get back on track as quickly as possible.

However, Rolfing is not exclusively for athletes, it simply takes a clear decision and a strong commitment to the program to get better. Many individuals who have been enduring pain for months or even years have found relief through my Rolfing program which is an enhanced 12-session program that combines Rolfing, Cranial Sacral Therapy, Rolf Movement Education, cross-training, nutrition coaching (upon request), and cutting-edge electronic therapies like PEMF or laser treatments (when necessary). I believe in a comprehensive holistic approach to healing, addressing not only the physical aspects of the pain but also the emotional and energetic components as well. This program is custom tailored to address your specific needs and to ensure that you receive safe, effective, and long-lasting results.

My commitment to all my clients' well-being extends beyond the treatment sessions. I prioritize education and empowerment, equipping my clients with the knowledge and tools they need to continue their progress independently. Whether you are an athlete striving for peak performance or an individual seeking to enhance your energy and overall quality of life, I am dedicated to helping you achieve your goals.

Choosing the right Certified Rolfer is crucial, as it requires trust and a personal connection. If my approach resonates with you and aligns with your needs and aspirations, I invite you to schedule a consultation. Together, we can embark on a journey towards a pain-free and vibrant life.

In conclusion, as a Certified Rolfer specializing in chronic pain and athletic performance, I am committed to helping my clients overcome pain, improve their energy levels, and enhance their quality of life. From professional athletes to individuals seeking relief from long-standing pain, I offer a tailor-made 12-session program that combine various techniques and therapies for effective and lasting results. If you are in search of a health provider who can guide you towards a pain-free and vibrant life, I encourage you to fill out the goals and outcomes questionnaire on my website so we can then discuss your specific goals and needs and how my program can serve you. 

Working with me you can expect to:

  • Reduce chronic pain,
  • Improve posture, balance and flexibility,
  • Feel stronger and more grounded,
  • Reduce recovery time between workouts,
  • Reduce chronic inflammation, 
  • Slow the aging process,
  • Reduce scar tissue adhesions after injuries or surgeries (if any),
  • Straighten scoliotic curves in the spine (if any),
  • Strengthen hips, knees, feet and ankles,
  • Dramatically reduce chances of future athletic injuries. 


If this looks, sounds or feels like possible fit for you, please visit my website at  www.DonatelliWellness.com to fill out the questionnaire.  You will then get a FREE, 15-min Telephone Consultation to discuss how my custom-tailored Rolfing program can help you. 

To Your Future Health, Wealth and Performance!


James J Donatelli
Chronic Pain Specialist, Certified Rolfer, Certified Rolf Movement Practitioner, Posture Alignment Specialist, Cranial Sacral Therapist, Certified Corporate Wellness Specialist, Latin Dance Instructor, Tony Robbins Sr Leader, Advanced Nutrition Coach, Cross-training Coach.

Profile:

Thom Shenk is a Certified Advanced Rolfer and Rolf Movement Practitioner. His combined knowledge and understanding of bodywork is eclectic in nature as he assists clients in freeing their bodies from pain, discomfort, tension and the effects of gravity on the body's structure.

Thom insightfully guides his clients to increase and expand their flexibility of movemen and ability to extend in gravity. Their vitality for life, and wholeness of the body, mind, emotions and spirit. He is also a graduate of the Baltimore school of massage and is nationally certified through the NCBTMB and a member of the American Massage Therapy Association.

He is well grounded in the scientific aspects of Rolfing with extensive understanding of anatomy, physiology and kinesiology. His awareness of the systems of the body is intentional. The classes he has taken have taught Thom about the muscles through Massage Therapy, the internal organs through Visceral Manipulation, the nerves through Neurofascial Release, the energy meridians with Jin Shin Jyutsu and the auric/energy body as a Reiki Master and Sekhem healing.

In his work Thom is compassionate, and also combines yearsof knowledge with his intuitive abilities. Thom is supportive of each client's goals for good health. He has also studied Cranio-Sacral Therapy and Matrix Energetics. He has given 60,000 bodywork sessions during his tenure.

Price

A session of Rolfing with Thom costs $115 for an hour and $155 for an hour and a half. There is a $2.50 surcharge added to the regular price for all credit card use. Visa, American Express, Discover and Mastercard are accepted. It is recommended that the sessions not be spaced any further than three weeks apart so the client can receive a sense of continuity and a better awareness of the effect of the Rolfing experience.

Additional Studies

Thom has also extensively studied the metaphysical technologies. He has practiced several forms of meditation since the early 1980's. Namely Zen and Tibetan meditations. He practiced Kundalini Yoga every day for five years and now continues with a weekly practice of yogas. He has familiarity with Yang style Tai Chi and Chi Gung. He began shamanic studies in 1984 and has had the honor of participating in more than 150 sweatlodge ceremonies with Yurock, Karouk, Cree, Lakota, Oglala, Apache, Cherokee, and Tiowa medicine men and women. He has also been on four vision quests.

Profile:

Congratulations!   You are definitely on the right track to pain relief and feeling better because you are looking for a Certified Rolfer.

Hello, my name is James Donatelli and I am a Chronic Pain and Athletic Performance Specialist. Throughout my decade of experience as a Certified Rolfer, I have witnessed the transformational power of Rolfing in countless individuals who were suffering from persistent pain that hindered their daily activities and enjoyment of life.

In my wellness center which is now located in Hypoluxo, Florida, I have had the privilege of working with a diverse range of clients, including athletes, active individuals, and those who simply want to lead a pain-free and vibrant life. No matter your background or the pain experienced, I believe that everyone deserves the opportunity to live their life to the fullest. As a specialist in chronic pain management, my primary goal is to help my clients alleviate their pain and regain their freedom of movement. As a performance specialist, my next goal is then to help your body perform at an even higher level to meet today's ever increasing demands from family, work and activities. 

For athletes, I understand the importance of optimal performance and recovery. Whether you are a tennis, baseball or soccer player, or any other kind of athlete that involves physical effort and precise movements, I can provide specialized assistance tailored to your specific needs. I am experienced in treating sports-related injuries, improving athletic performance, and helping high-achievers who care about performance up their game and get back on track as quickly as possible.

However, Rolfing is not exclusively for athletes, it simply takes a clear decision and a strong commitment to the program to get better. Many individuals who have been enduring pain for months or even years have found relief through my Rolfing program which is an enhanced 12-session program that combines Rolfing, Cranial Sacral Therapy, Rolf Movement Education, cross-training, nutrition coaching (upon request), and cutting-edge electronic therapies like PEMF or laser treatments (when necessary). I believe in a comprehensive holistic approach to healing, addressing not only the physical aspects of the pain but also the emotional and energetic components as well. This program is custom tailored to address your specific needs and to ensure that you receive safe, effective, and long-lasting results.

My commitment to all my clients' well-being extends beyond the treatment sessions. I prioritize education and empowerment, equipping my clients with the knowledge and tools they need to continue their progress independently. Whether you are an athlete striving for peak performance or an individual seeking to enhance your energy and overall quality of life, I am dedicated to helping you achieve your goals.

Choosing the right Certified Rolfer is crucial, as it requires trust and a personal connection. If my approach resonates with you and aligns with your needs and aspirations, I invite you to schedule a consultation. Together, we can embark on a journey towards a pain-free and vibrant life.

In conclusion, as a Certified Rolfer specializing in chronic pain and athletic performance, I am committed to helping my clients overcome pain, improve their energy levels, and enhance their quality of life. From professional athletes to individuals seeking relief from long-standing pain, I offer a tailor-made 12-session program that combine various techniques and therapies for effective and lasting results. If you are in search of a health provider who can guide you towards a pain-free and vibrant life, I encourage you to fill out the goals and outcomes questionnaire on my website so we can then discuss your specific goals and needs and how my program can serve you. 

Working with me you can expect to:

  • Reduce chronic pain,
  • Improve posture, balance and flexibility,
  • Feel stronger and more grounded,
  • Reduce recovery time between workouts,
  • Reduce chronic inflammation, 
  • Slow the aging process,
  • Reduce scar tissue adhesions after injuries or surgeries (if any),
  • Straighten scoliotic curves in the spine (if any),
  • Strengthen hips, knees, feet and ankles,
  • Dramatically reduce chances of future athletic injuries. 


If this looks, sounds or feels like possible fit for you, please visit my website at  www.DonatelliWellness.com to fill out the questionnaire.  You will then get a FREE, 15-min Telephone Consultation to discuss how my custom-tailored Rolfing program can help you. 

To Your Future Health, Wealth and Performance!

Profile:

My goal is to create ease in movement for all bodies.  As a Rolfer and movement educator, I understand how to facilitate restoration and maximum potential in a body, and I aim to share my experience to enable others on their own journeys toward ease. 

I work with clients to relieve injuries, harmful and painful postural habits, and movement restrictions through specialized manual therapy and movement analysis. Through this integrative approach, the body can now operate with a healthier pattern of function and balance.

At an early age I developed an understanding of the body's need for structural integrity without strain through my ballet and modern dance training. I also gained an appreciation for the kind of care and attention the body requires in order to live comfortably and to prevent injury.  

I discovered Rolfing Structural Integration when my body had become painful and unmanageable despite my best efforts at self-care. Rolfing helped me develop a whole new level of potential and ease in my body that I never knew was possible.  

I believe that all bodies have the potential for ease in movement regardless of medical history or physical fitness and it can be found through a journey of transformation.

Office locations in Lower Fairfield County, Connecticut and New York City.

Member of the International Association of Structural Integrators (IASI) & the Dr. Ida Rolf Institute® (DIRI).

Profile:

As a Certified Advanced Rolfer?, I help my clients restore their body's natural movement through structural alignment interventions and holistic bodywork. Every body is different, so the starting point, speed of transition, and outcome of the work will be unique to each client.

Education

· The Rolf Institute® of Structural Integration, Boulder, Colorado

· Primitive reflexive movements (embryological and early development)

· Space awareness body-mapping with SourcePoint Therapy®

· Cranial Sacral Therapy

· Diaphragmatic releasing and balancing

· Yoga, Thai Chi and Qi-Gong


After years of athletics?gymnastics, two marathons, acrobatics, dancing, lacrosse, fencing and music?I began to notice pain in my body. I found myself wanting a more balanced and individual approach to body development and awareness. In my search for sustainable health, I received the Rolfing® Ten Series and have been studying and advocating Rolfing® Structural Integration ever since.

When the body is out of structural balance, movement is harder and often causes excessive wear and pain. Through Rolfing® I felt as though the forces of gravity were on my side. Instead of working against my body, everyday movements became easier and pain-free. As my body slowly changed (and continues to change), my ideas about health, healing and personal growth have been transformed.

Along with relief from pain from a sports injury, I found a renewed sense of enjoyment in simple daily activities. I was amazed?not only had the pain subsided, but I found a calming sense of ease and grace in my movements. I want to help you find the same.

Aloha!  

Welcome to my Rolfing - Structural Integration practice on the Big Island of Hawaii. I was lucky enough to find a line of work that I am passionate about, and am very happy that I get to share my love of our anatomy (and the mirade ways that it functions) with so many different types of people... and in such an amazing place!
(My acupuncturist husband did a great job building our new office in Ocean View. Come on down south and check it out!)

I became a Licensed Massage Therapist in 1995. I have been a Certified Rolfer and Rolf Movement Practitioner since 2006, and received my Advanced Rolfing Certification in 2010.

I look forward to helping you to be more balanced and comfortable with yourself so that you can enjoy the experience of being in your body.

Visit our website or give me a call for more information.  A hui hou!

Profile:

I discovered Rolfing® in 1980 after recovering from back surgery. The surgery allowed me to walk again but I often still had severe pain. This Rolfing® experience alleviated my ongoing pain by resolving the old injuries and compensations which lead to the crippling back pain and eventual surgery. This experience and an ongoing interest in the human body, movement as an athlete and ski coach lead me to begin my Rolfing training in 1985. I received my basic certification in 1987, finished my Advanced Rolfing Certification in 1993, and received my Movement certification in 2002. I am on the faculty of the Rolf Institute® and have conducted classes with students from all over the world. I also have over 800 hours of training in biodynamic craniosacral therapy and integrate its subtle evoking with the direct contact of Rolfing®.



My clients have included Olympic medalists in both track and field and skiing. My nearly 40 years of teaching and coaching skiing is an asset in working with athletes, especially young competitive skiers. Because of my years of back pain, I love helping folks who are in chronic pain. Particularly rewarding is helping people to resolve severe trauma and working with autistic children.

Profile:

Welcome to an amazing embodiment experience!  I first learned about Rolfing® in the early 1990s and was instantly drawn to its logic, strategy, and results. Over the years I have been inspired and transformed by this work, and am grateful and excited to be a part of the Rolfing community in Dayton, Ohio. Since graduating from the Dr. Ida Rolf Institute of Structural Integration® I have helped clients release deeply ingrained tension due to neck and back pain, scoliosis, impaired mobility, repetitive stress injuries, and other chronic strain patterns. My youngest client so far is six years old and my oldest is a thriving 92 years old. I have also been teaching health and fitness classes for over 30 years and proudly served in the Air Force for 28 years. 

I'm currently accepting new clients and offer sessions late mornings, evenings, and weekends. Please contact me via phone/text at (916) 201--6810 or email me at mdailey30@hotmail.com for more information. I look forward to hearing from you and am excited to go on this transformational journey with you towards your self-awareness and embodiment.

Profile:
I've been practicing in Northern Virginia since 1980. I've completed the Rolf® Basic training in 1980 and Advanced training in 1995 and 2007. After 36 years of practice, I have  come to view Rolfing not as a technique, but as a point of view. It is an attempt to understand how bodies live and function in gravity, in physical space. My belief is that changes in physical position should increase mobility that ultimately leads to increased vitality. Overtime, the level of complexity of my clients has necessitated  a broad range of study. As a result, I have studied many different modalities; from various Osteopathic and energetic traditions and theories to biomechanics. Over the last couple of years, I have been investigating the effects of nerves on structure and function as well as biomechanical approaches that arose from Osteopathic traditions. I work with and refer to a broad range of traditional and integrative medical practitioners including medical doctors, osteopaths, chiropractors, psychotherapists, nutritionists, dentists, physical and massage therapists and acupuncturists.

I have and continue to serve in a number of leadership  capacities. I was the regional Clinical Director in the Washington, DC area for American Whole Health as well as being on their Health Care Policy Council. I am past President of the Rolf Institute and have worked with the Federation of Massage Therapy, Bodywork and Somatic Practice as well as the Board of Directors of the National Certification Board of Therapeutic Massage Therapy and Bodywork (NCBTMB).  I currently serve on the Board of Directors for the Ida P. Rolf Research Foundation.

Profile:
Helen Goodrum (Rolfer, BCTMB) is a movement educator, practitioner, and optimizer serving Arizona, USA. She brings her embodied practice spanning over three decades to her clients at Artful Healthcare in Prescott, Arizona.

An international performer with The Carpetbag Brigade Physical Theater, student of the Axis Syllabus International Research Community and a Contact Improvisation dancer, Helen's ongoing research of the human body, movement education, perception & coordination are supported by her qualifications as a Rolfer®, Rolf Movement® practitioner, Franklin Method Pelvic Floor Trainer, CranioSacral 1 (biomechanical) Therapist and Contemporary Dancer.

Helen is further inspired and educated by her studies with Tom Myers Anatomy Trains®, Bonnie Bainbridge Cohen Body-Mind Centering®, Feldenkrais Method® and Bones for Life®.

Helen has traveled the world extensively, enjoys performing to theater audiences, loves hiking, and unwinds by relaxing with a good book and cup of tea from her motherland England.

I have been Rolfing for over 40 years, most of that time in medical practices.  I became a Certified Advanced Rolfer in 1983, Rolf Movement practitioner in '85', trained in Cranial-Sacral therapy starting in the early 80's, and in Visceral (organ) manipulation since the early 90's.  When appropriate, I find applying these various modalities, as well as my psychological/trauma training, enables me to more effectively achieve the goals of Rolfing with my clients.

Bethany Ward, MBA is dual faculty at the Rolf Institute of Structural Integration in the Rolfing and Rolf Movement Integration departments. She is past-president of the Ida P. I have been practicing Rolfing since 1973. Caryn is the co-author (with Kevin Frank) of How Life Moves, Explorations in Meaning and Body Awareness, and collaborated on the book Bodystories, A Guide to Experiential Anatomy, by Andrea Olsen a book based on the course Caryn created at Middlebury College. 
Caryn has a private practice in bodywork and structural integration from a perceptual and coordinative point of view for over 35 years and teaches in the US and Internationally.

Profile:

Congratulations!   You are definitely on the right track to pain relief and feeling better because you are looking for a Certified Rolfer.

Hello, my name is James Donatelli and I am a Chronic Pain and Athletic Performance Specialist. Throughout my decade of experience as a Certified Rolfer, I have witnessed the transformational power of Rolfing in countless individuals who were suffering from persistent pain that hindered their daily activities and enjoyment of life.

In my wellness center which is now located in Hypoluxo, Florida, I have had the privilege of working with a diverse range of clients, including athletes, active individuals, and those who simply want to lead a pain-free and vibrant life. No matter your background or the pain experienced, I believe that everyone deserves the opportunity to live their life to the fullest. As a specialist in chronic pain management, my primary goal is to help my clients alleviate their pain and regain their freedom of movement. As a performance specialist, my next goal is then to help your body perform at an even higher level to meet today's ever increasing demands from family, work and activities. 

For athletes, I understand the importance of optimal performance and recovery. Whether you are a tennis, baseball or soccer player, or any other kind of athlete that involves physical effort and precise movements, I can provide specialized assistance tailored to your specific needs. I am experienced in treating sports-related injuries, improving athletic performance, and helping high-achievers who care about performance up their game and get back on track as quickly as possible.

However, Rolfing is not exclusively for athletes, it simply takes a clear decision and a strong commitment to the program to get better. Many individuals who have been enduring pain for months or even years have found relief through my Rolfing program which is an enhanced 12-session program that combines Rolfing, Cranial Sacral Therapy, Rolf Movement Education, cross-training, nutrition coaching (upon request), and cutting-edge electronic therapies like PEMF or laser treatments (when necessary). I believe in a comprehensive holistic approach to healing, addressing not only the physical aspects of the pain but also the emotional and energetic components as well. This program is custom tailored to address your specific needs and to ensure that you receive safe, effective, and long-lasting results.

My commitment to all my clients' well-being extends beyond the treatment sessions. I prioritize education and empowerment, equipping my clients with the knowledge and tools they need to continue their progress independently. Whether you are an athlete striving for peak performance or an individual seeking to enhance your energy and overall quality of life, I am dedicated to helping you achieve your goals.

Choosing the right Certified Rolfer is crucial, as it requires trust and a personal connection. If my approach resonates with you and aligns with your needs and aspirations, I invite you to schedule a consultation. Together, we can embark on a journey towards a pain-free and vibrant life.

In conclusion, as a Certified Rolfer specializing in chronic pain and athletic performance, I am committed to helping my clients overcome pain, improve their energy levels, and enhance their quality of life. From professional athletes to individuals seeking relief from long-standing pain, I offer a tailor-made 12-session program that combine various techniques and therapies for effective and lasting results. If you are in search of a health provider who can guide you towards a pain-free and vibrant life, I encourage you to fill out the goals and outcomes questionnaire on my website so we can then discuss your specific goals and needs and how my program can serve you. 

Working with me you can expect to:

  • Reduce chronic pain,
  • Improve posture, balance and flexibility,
  • Feel stronger and more grounded,
  • Reduce recovery time between workouts,
  • Reduce chronic inflammation, 
  • Slow the aging process,
  • Reduce scar tissue adhesions after injuries or surgeries (if any),
  • Straighten scoliotic curves in the spine (if any),
  • Strengthen hips, knees, feet and ankles,
  • Dramatically reduce chances of future athletic injuries. 


If this looks, sounds or feels like possible fit for you, please visit my website at  www.DonatelliWellness.com to fill out the questionnaire.  You will then get a FREE, 15-min Telephone Consultation to discuss how my custom-tailored Rolfing program can help you. 

To Your Future Health, Wealth and Performance!


James J Donatelli
Chronic Pain Specialist, Certified Rolfer, Certified Rolf Movement Practitioner, Posture Alignment Specialist, Cranial Sacral Therapist, Certified Corporate Wellness Specialist, Latin Dance Instructor, Tony Robbins Sr Leader, Advanced Nutrition Coach, Cross-training Coach.

My practice in Rolfing® Structural Integration has facilitated so many lovely and strong clients in releasing postural constriction. Even more than that, I am proud to be of service to the holistic purpose! Aligning a client with their goals of freedom of movement and deeper sensual awareness of their energy patterns is a real passion for me. Along with hands-on work, I use language and metaphor, movement education, and exploration to shift the stuck meanings and gestures from the holding patterns that have lost usefulness.
 
Ceridwen has worked fifteen years as a Certified Rolfer in Atlanta, Chattanooga, Los Angeles, and now Providence, Rhode Island.  Her writing spans topics from storytelling to holistic healing to Rolfing SI to re-imagining a new world. In the next few months, her first book, a memoir will be done and hopefully published forthwith. It follows Ceridwen on a life-changing pilgrimage full of courage, trauma, healing, and forgiveness to Scotland back in 2011. 

I also offer discussions and workshops to small and large groups who are interested in the concepts and possibilities of Rolfing Structural Integration, stretching techniques (my own), scoliosis, and loose joints.

"Last year I was confronted with a difficult decision on choosing treatment for an injury I sustained to discs in my lower back. Both the prospect of surgery and or a shot of steroids to my spine left me mortified. After much consideration and research I connected with Brett and we began a ten session series of Rolfing. I wasn't sure of what to expect exactly, but the idea of starting from the ground up and realigning the building blocks of my body seemed like a good way to begin. Brett's communication with me throughout my series was impressive. I was always aware of what we were working on and what what we were trying to achieve. Not only was I aware, but was able to see for myself the progress achieved due to the photo journal we kept, as well as Brett's inquiries on how I felt in between sessions. Armed with an abundance of information and a little "home work," I was feeling better every time I left. I began to move with more confidence and was conscience of little changes that had, by the end of the series, literally changed my stride and posture. I am sincerely grateful to Brett for the time, energy and knowledge he instilled in me, enabling me to forgo the small yet terrifying risks associated with other, more invasive procedures that I am sure would have left me on a much more different road down life. Thank you and keep on Rolfing!?

  - Douglas Byers

"I recently had the pleasure of working with Brett Linder, Certified Rolfer and Rolf Movement Practitioner.  I was in a bad way when I turned to Brett for relief for what began as pain in the top of one foot that felt like a bone was out of place. Pain was spreading to my other foot, probably because I was favoring my injured foot and overusing the other, by the time I saw Brett for the first time. I was also beginning to have back pain because when ones feet are out of kilter,  it can throw the back out of whack, too.  I had seen my family doctor and a podiatrist for the problem but had gotten no relief.  They were suggesting PT, which, from my own past experience, I knew could be a long process. 

Having such a depth of understanding of anatomy and physiology, Brett knew at what point I was paining and where to focus his work physically on my feet as a Rolf Movement Practitioner, but he did so much more than that--something I had never before understood. Brett helped me to create an image of what relaxation meant to me.  As a healer, he instinctively knew that just exhorting me to "relax" would never do it for me!  Learning that I was from Florida, Brett, asked if that meant I enjoyed the water.  When I told him that I had spent every summer of my youth floating on the waves, he asked me to recall the feelings of those pleasant times and to remember how my feet felt as I bobbed ever so lightly up and down in the surf. It was when I was able to recreate that feeling of relaxation that Brett was able to really work with my feet.  It was when I had a concept of what it meant to relax and I was able to recreate it for myself in practice at home as I had in only one session with Brett  that any pain I had began to abate. Brett motivated me to work on stretching exercises every morning and, after only a few days, maybe even a week, I had no pain at all.  I shall never be able to thank him enough.  Having a therapist partner with me and gently talk me through the process restored my sense of well-being as well as the use of my feet.  I don't know if all Rolfers do this, but Brett does and it is very therapeutic!  

Frankly, I was wondering if the pain would return.  I'm still doing the exercises Brett suggested I do because they feel good and help me to have confidence in the process and am happy to report that I have had absolutely no sign of the pain returning. 
 
I would highly recommend Brett Linder.  I plan on going for the "Ten Series" now.  I don't believe I need to be "suffering" for a Rolf Movement Practioner (Brett Linder) to be of assistance.  I want to be in better touch with my body and the relationship between my body and mind and believe that Brett can help me with this."

I hurt daily. Usually, I would start my day with an anti-inflammatory. Then I would come home from work, take an Epsom salt bath, and massage my feet with arnica gel (a natural pain reliever).

One leg felt super tight and balled-up, while the other leg moved with such ease. I went back for a 10-series. A 10-series goes through different sections of your body, in 90 minute increments. So, one session is all legs; another is ribs, shoulders, arms and hips; another is the sides of your body; another is chest, arms and head; and another is the back of the body-from the calves up to the back. Think of the amount that can be accomplished in 90 minutes for each section of your body! 

The result: At the end of each session, I would stand up, walk around, and be completely astonished at how much lighter my body felt, and at the ease with which it moved. The best part is that I am still feeling the benefits. I no longer take an anti-inflammatory for breakfast and I haven't taken an Epsom salt bath in a month. CEO of Balance Orlando and Empower Yoga in Orlando, FL

Sondra is passionate about helping people reduce pain and improve their overall well-being with an integrative treatment approach. 

Her educational background and experience include a balance of business and bodywork.   She has hundreds of hours in trainings in massage therapy, holding several certifications in Myofascial release, Thai massage, and deep tissue work. 

In addition, she has extensive training in different modalities of yoga.   As the CEO of Empower Yoga, she has trained and taught yoga teachers to take a practical approach to yoga movement with an emphasis on correcting structural alignment to help clients reduce their risk of injury and improve their strength and mobility in a safe manner. 

In her prior life, she was a corporate accountant.   Her analytical approach shows in both her operations and her bodywork treatments. 

After a series of car accidents and years of chronic tension from long hours at a desk, she searched for relief of pain.   She found a combination of intentional movement and advance therapeutic bodywork to be the answer.  This fueled her mission to learn as much as she could and help others find relief from tension and pain.

Profile:

Heidi Massa (BA, JD, University of Chicago),  Certified Advanced Rolfer and Rolf Movement Practitoner, has guided the somatic adventures of the discerning, the curious and the brave since 1994 in Chicago's East Lincoln Park.  She's a function-oriented practitioner; and her client-centered approach is tailored to meet your particular needs, interests, and way of being in the world -- not to conform to any particular viewpoint.  You can expect:

  • Fun, challenge and discovery
  • Exploring questions you might never have asked before
  • Access to real options you might not have thought possible

In-person consultations are always free of charge.

 

Heidi trained through the Rolf Institute in Munich, Germany and Sao Paulo, Brazil:

  • Certified Advanced Rolfer 2000
  • Rolf Movement Practitioner 1995
  • Certified   Rolfer 1994

 

Continuing Education: Heidi studied extensively with Hubert Godard over several years to learn the strategies and techniques of his game-changing theory of tonic function. In addition to using the tonic function approach in movement sessions, Heidi makes it a key component of her structural sessions, movement awareness being essential to recognizing, using and maintaining changes made through hands-on work.  Heidi has additional specialized training in other topics, including:

  • Biomechanics of limbs and axial complex
  • Berry® Method
  • Move in Mind®
  • Tensegrity Touch
  • Osteopathic approaches to low back pain
  • Cranial, neural and visceral work
  • Interventions with oral reflex functions

 

Professional Activities: Heidi has served on the Rolf Institute's Ethics & Business Practices Committee since 1997; worked with its Law & Legislation Committee for several years following its inception in 2007; and acted as an editor for the Journal of Structural Integration since 2001. Member, ISMETA (International Somatic movement Education & Therapy Ass'n).

    Michelle has over 12 years experience as a licensed massage therapist, Yoga instructor and Reiki 1 practitioner. Her interest in holistic body work sparked at a young age of 15 during her competitive swimming years. After recovering from a partial knee replacement surgery, her inner awareness of subtle sensations sparked during physical therapy sessions. She became interested in how the body was deteriorating during the recovery process in a straight leg brace and what it took to build muscle, coordination and trust back up afterwards. It was the process of healing which led her to fall in love with the study of human anatomy and how the body is put together to function as a whole.
    Her background provides a felt educational touch to the physical and energetic body offering a unique healing experience. Michelle's passion for physical health, and her innate understanding of the human body helps assure each session to be tailored to fit the individual client and their bodies needs. She has an extensive background in movement exploration from years training at Ape co Movement School in Denver and Boulder, Colorado. Michelle often incorporates and shares her movement / conditioning skills with her clients to support the work done in a Traditional Rolfing 10 series.

Profile:
Since completing my training at The Rolf Institute in 2003, I have worked with a wide range of clients to achieve more with their bodies and recover from injury, overuse, and trauma.
As a practitioner, I am interested in how subtle movement patterns and perception can powerfully shape structural relationships in the body. I incorporate methods of working that harness the body's innate responsiveness and intelligence to create precise structural change. This results in an experience that is more comfortable and often longer-lasting than when change is forced on the body.
Like most Rolfers, my journey to the profession began as a client. I developed osteoarthritis in one ankle after an injury, and in my early twenties, I was in increasingly chronic pain and discomfort throughout my body. I felt tense, old, and unhappy as the patterns of compensation and strain from limping and favoring my ankle caused increasing chaos in my body as a whole.
Rolfing brought me to a point where the ankle joint issues no longer dominated my movement and posture and I could walk not only without the strain that had been exhausting me, but also with a quality of balance and an ease that I hadn't known before. I was attracted to the way the work felt like both a science and an art: a hands-on craft that gave him deep, precise shifts toward a new way of moving in the world and experiencing myself.
Since my initial training as a Rolfer, I continue to explore methods and modalities that support whole-body organization and healing, with a particular focus in recent years on Biodynamic Craniosacral Therapy.
I am grateful to have a Rolfing as a life long vocation, a profession that provides me with a way to continuously learn, practice and help people.

Profile:
Nobuko Muth
Objective
To work within a health conscious community to apply my wide range of professional skills as a Rolfer® and massage practitioner to help clients with relaxation and tension reduction or with more challenging physical needs.
Professional skills
Rolfing? for Structural Integration and Rolf Movement®, 2000 to present
As a private practitioner over 12 years in Tokyo with Japanese and Western cliental. My aim was to evoke clients body-balance with yield holding pattern and connecting hold body.
Craniosacral Biodynamics, 1996 to present
I studied Craniosacral practice under Jim Asher, Tom Shaver, D.O. and James Jealous, D.O. I designed special treatments for children with learning disabled, cerebral palsy and spinocerebellar degeneration (SCD) using these procedures.
Bodynamic massage (Body-Mind Integrative Massage ), 2010 to present
Bodynamic is a body-centered developmental psychotherapy originated in Denmark. This massage work on the body-mind connection provides therapeutic interventions with significant specificity. After the recent tsunami and earthquake disaster(2011), I was able to help many people to reduce tension and anxiety while potentially improving sleep quality.
Visceral Manipulation (Digestive, Urinary, Respiratory)
I usually include this in my Rolfing session as needed. Some doctors referred post-surgery clients to me.
Pre-Natal Massage and Postpartum body care
I worked at maternity hospital for about two years taking care of women's pre/post birth physical needs using Rolfing, Craniosacral and Bodynamics techniques as needed.
Energy Therapies?Energetic Osteopathy, Esoteric healing)
At the start of a session, I always take time to sense and connect with the client's energy field and reach toward their centers and to understand their needs. 
Teaching / Workshops
I gave Rolfing and Movement workshops attended by 10 - 30 people once a month for 9 years. Also taught myofascial release to professional bodyworkers (physical therapists, Aroma treatment therapists, Acupuncturists, etc.).

Profile:

Named after its founder, Dr. Ida P. Rolf, Rolfing Structural Integration is a form of bodywork that reorganizes the connective tissues, called fascia, that permeate the entire body.
More than fifty years ago, Dr. Rolf recognized that the body is inherently a system of seamless networks of tissues rather than a collection of separate parts.  

Essentially, the Rolfing SI process enables the body to regain the natural integrity of its form, thus enhancing postural efficiency and your freedom of movement. 

Please contact me directly for additional information about my practice.

Rolfing Structural Integration is a method of deep manipulation of the connective tissues of the body, developed by Dr. Ida P. Rolf. Her intention was to create a system of postural restructuring and movement re-patterning, in order to promote ease and balance in the body with a corresponding effect on the mind. Profile:

Rolfing Structural Integration is a method of deep manipulation of the connective tissues of the body, developed by Dr. Ida P. Rolf. Her intention was to create a system of postural restructuring and movement re-patterning, in order to promote ease and balance in the body with a corresponding effect on the mind. A Rolfer is highly trained to see, and address the complex ways in which a body-mind is relating to itself and its environment. The more balanced these relationships are, the more choice we will have in our experience. Through hands-on manipulation, and movement (perceptual) education, Rolfing is a very precise and effective way to change deep-set habits of posture, movement, and orientation.
Rolfing Structural Integration is a method of deep manipulation of the connective tissues of the body, developed by Dr. Ida P. Rolf. Her intention was to create a system of postural restructuring and movement re-patterning, in order to promote ease and balance in the body and therefore the mind. A Rolfer is highly trained to see, and address the complex ways in which a body-mind is relating to itself and its environment. The more balanced these relationships are, the more choice we will have in our experience. Through hands-on manipulation, and movement (perceptual) education, Rolfing is a very precise and effective way to change deep-set habits of posture, movement, and orientation.

Profile:

As an active outdoor enthusiast Deanna found her way down the path of bodywork and healing when she addressed her own sports injuries so she could get back to playing in the mountains. Deanna became a bodywork practitioner so that she could help others do the same. In 2003 she started her somatic practice & in 2010 she became a Certified RolferTM & Rolf Movement® Practitioner. As a seeker, Deanna's journey has been about more than just athletics & outdoor enthusiasm. Embracing the bigger questions of life, Deanna seeks reconnection within our most deeply relational selves; as an ecosystem, spirit & soul, and as humanity. Integrating the structural work of Rolfing with the coherency-regulation work of Somatic Experiencing®, and the subtle-energetic work of Craniosacral, Sourpoint®, & clairvoyant visioning, creates a way of working globally with the whole person as a whole person. To hold all the aspects and parts from any contact point, to grasp and guide the patterns that lead to deep change and transformation, for the good of all beings, so that we may enjoy our lives, and live our purpose to its fullest.

Profile:

District Rolfing

 My practice is centered on helping people from all backgrounds, ages, and levels of physical condition feel better in their bodies.   I offer the classic 10-series and individual Rolfing sessions, integrating in visceral and neural manipulation, and movement to best meet the needs of each person.  I also offer separate visceral and neural manipulation and movement sessions.  The visceral and neural work is often especially beneficially to those with prior injuries or physical trauma (including car crashes or whiplash), surgeries, or childbirth that they have not completely recovered from.    I am located in Woodley Park in Northwest Washington DC, right by the Red Line metro .  

I have over 15 years experience in holistic, structural bodywork.   In addition to being a certified Rolfer, I am currently pursuing advanced Rolfing training and also have training in visceral and neural manipulation from the Barral Institute.  Prior to studying Rolfing I had extensive experience in therapeutic Thai bodywork, including nerve massage and abdominal massage.

Congratulations!   You are definitely on the right track to pain relief and feeling better because you are looking for a Certified Rolfer.

Hello, my name is James Donatelli and I am a Chronic Pain and Athletic Performance Specialist. Throughout my decade of experience as a Certified Rolfer, I have witnessed the transformational power of Rolfing in countless individuals who were suffering from persistent pain that hindered their daily activities and enjoyment of life.

In my wellness center which is now located in Hypoluxo, Florida, I have had the privilege of working with a diverse range of clients, including athletes, active individuals, and those who simply want to lead a pain-free and vibrant life. No matter your background or the pain experienced, I believe that everyone deserves the opportunity to live their life to the fullest. As a specialist in chronic pain management, my primary goal is to help my clients alleviate their pain and regain their freedom of movement. As a performance specialist, my next goal is then to help your body perform at an even higher level to meet today's ever increasing demands from family, work and activities. 

For athletes, I understand the importance of optimal performance and recovery. Whether you are a tennis, baseball or soccer player, or any other kind of athlete that involves physical effort and precise movements, I can provide specialized assistance tailored to your specific needs. I am experienced in treating sports-related injuries, improving athletic performance, and helping high-achievers who care about performance up their game and get back on track as quickly as possible.

However, Rolfing is not exclusively for athletes, it simply takes a clear decision and a strong commitment to the program to get better. Many individuals who have been enduring pain for months or even years have found relief through my Rolfing program which is an enhanced 12-session program that combines Rolfing, Cranial Sacral Therapy, Rolf Movement Education, cross-training, nutrition coaching (upon request), and cutting-edge electronic therapies like PEMF or laser treatments (when necessary). I believe in a comprehensive holistic approach to healing, addressing not only the physical aspects of the pain but also the emotional and energetic components as well. This program is custom tailored to address your specific needs and to ensure that you receive safe, effective, and long-lasting results.

My commitment to all my clients' well-being extends beyond the treatment sessions. I prioritize education and empowerment, equipping my clients with the knowledge and tools they need to continue their progress independently. Whether you are an athlete striving for peak performance or an individual seeking to enhance your energy and overall quality of life, I am dedicated to helping you achieve your goals.

Choosing the right Certified Rolfer is crucial, as it requires trust and a personal connection. If my approach resonates with you and aligns with your needs and aspirations, I invite you to schedule a consultation. Together, we can embark on a journey towards a pain-free and vibrant life.

In conclusion, as a Certified Rolfer specializing in chronic pain and athletic performance, I am committed to helping my clients overcome pain, improve their energy levels, and enhance their quality of life. From professional athletes to individuals seeking relief from long-standing pain, I offer a tailor-made 12-session program that combine various techniques and therapies for effective and lasting results. If you are in search of a health provider who can guide you towards a pain-free and vibrant life, I encourage you to fill out the goals and outcomes questionnaire on my website so we can then discuss your specific goals and needs and how my program can serve you. 

Working with me you can expect to:

  • Reduce chronic pain,
  • Improve posture, balance and flexibility,
  • Feel stronger and more grounded,
  • Reduce recovery time between workouts,
  • Reduce chronic inflammation, 
  • Slow the aging process,
  • Reduce scar tissue adhesions after injuries or surgeries (if any),
  • Straighten scoliotic curves in the spine (if any),
  • Strengthen hips, knees, feet and ankles,
  • Dramatically reduce chances of future athletic injuries. 


If this looks, sounds or feels like possible fit for you, please visit my website at  www.DonatelliWellness.com to fill out the questionnaire.  You will then get a FREE, 15-min Telephone Consultation to discuss how my custom-tailored Rolfing program can help you. 

To Your Future Health, Wealth and Performance!


James J Donatelli
Chronic Pain Specialist, Certified Rolfer, Certified Rolf Movement Practitioner, Posture Alignment Specialist, Cranial Sacral Therapist, Certified Corporate Wellness Specialist, Latin Dance Instructor, Tony Robbins Sr Leader, Advanced Nutrition Coach, Cross-training Coach.

Profile:

As a Certified Advanced Rolfer?, I help my clients restore their body's natural movement through structural alignment interventions and holistic bodywork. Every body is different, so the starting point, speed of transition, and outcome of the work will be unique to each client.

 

Education

· The Rolf Institute® of Structural Integration, Boulder, Colorado

· Primitive reflexive movements (embryological and early development)

· Space awareness body-mapping with SourcePoint Therapy®

· Cranial Sacral Therapy

· Diaphragmatic releasing and balancing

· Yoga, Thai Chi and Qi-Gong


After years of athletics?gymnastics, two marathons, acrobatics, dancing, lacrosse, fencing and music?I began to notice pain in my body. I found myself wanting a more balanced and individual approach to body development and awareness. In my search for sustainable health, I received the Rolfing® Ten Series and have been studying and advocating Rolfing® Structural Integration ever since.

 

When the body is out of structural balance, movement is harder and often causes excessive wear and pain. Through Rolfing® I felt as though the forces of gravity were on my side. Instead of working against my body, everyday movements became easier and pain-free. As my body slowly changed (and continues to change), my ideas about health, healing and personal growth have been transformed.

 

Along with relief from pain from a sports injury, I found a renewed sense of enjoyment in simple daily activities. I was amazed?not only had the pain subsided, but I found a calming sense of ease and grace in my movements. I want to help you find the same.

My training includes Visceral Manipulation and techniques from Manual Osteopathy with Peter Schwind & Dr Alain Croibier in Munich, Germany, and advanced principles of strain-counterstrain from the Advanced training with Tessy Brungart and Brian Tuckey's Jones Fascial Counterstrain.  My continuing education, in the US, has been with in osteopathic manual technique with students of Barrall, Upledger, Jones, & Ron Murray (Rolfer also teaching osteopathic technique in Canada). 

My approach is rational and holistic, and I offer both biomechanical problem-solving and classical 10-session work. 

I have six years of experience working as a bodywork contractor with the US Military, and I offer discounts for active duty military and law enforcement personnel. My practice is informed by practice of classical Japanese martial arts, fascination with biology, science and the natural world.

 I am 1994 graduate of the University of Mary with a Bachelor's Degree in Athletic Training and Biology in 1994.  I also am also a 2013 graduate of Kent State University - Ashtabula with an Associates Degree as a Physical Therapist Assistant.  I am currently licensed in the State of Michigan as a Physical Therapist Assistant and Massage Therapist and am a Retired Athletic Trainer.  

I have been working in the Physical Therapy/Bodywork field for almost 30 years including areas of Chronic Pain, Sports Medicine, Orthopedic Rehabilitation and Pediatrics.  I have trained in a variety of manual therapy techniques with her main emphasis on Structural Integration, Fascial Release, Craniosacral Therapy and Reflexology.  I  am an Advanced Structural Integration Practioner and trained with Emmett Hutchins.  I am also is a Level 2 Certified Foundation Training Instructor which is a functional decompression technique to helping with proper body mechanics and fascial alignment.  

Throughout my career my focus has been on understanding body mechanics of how the body moves and functions.  I incorporate that knowledge to find the best treatment approach for my clients.  My treatments include postural assessment, movement analysis, manual therapy techniques and client education.  My ultimate goal is to educate clients on effective methods for improving how their body moves and functions helping reduce injury and improve overall quality of life.  

My practice is by appointment only so contact her directly by either email or phone to find out more.

Profile:

I am a Certified Rolfer and Rolf Movement Practitioner, and received my certification for the original method of Structural Integration from the Rolf Institute in Boulder, Colorado, in 2004. I have been practicing bodywork in San Francisco since 2002, and I have my own practice in the Glen Park neighborhood of San Francisco. I am also a Certified Massage Therapist trained in Swedish Massage, Myofascial Release Technique, Sports Injury and Post Surgical Rehabilitation, Visceral Manipulation, Orthopedic Massage, and Trigger Point Therapy, which I integrate into my Rolfing practice. 

The realm of the senses, the human body, the complexity of the psyche, health, fitness and the achievement of happiness and wellbeing have always captivated me and compelled me to explore the healing arts.

A severe car accident in my twenties left me with a hip that was extremely limited in it’s range of motion and I suffered a constant low-grade pain that motivated me to try just about everything that promised me relief – even if just short-term. After exploring many different physical therapy modalities I discovered Rolfing.

Rolfing brought me the most significant results in a surprisingly short period of time and restored my wellbeing. The changes I experienced in my body were so significant that I decided to make a career change in order to help others find relief from pain, regain physical strength, achieve freedom of movement - and, most of all, discover the joy of their bodies in equilibrium.

Inspiration, empowerment, and enthusiasm are gifts I received from my teachers and mentors, which I strive to pass on to my clients. Although Rolfing is the core of my practice, I draw upon the full spectrum of my training, life experiences and knowledge to help my clients grow and enjoy better health in their daily lives. I educate, facilitate and foster awareness in my clients to help them improve their quality of life by living in harmony with their minds, bodies and spirits. My approach is methodical and goal-oriented, intuitive and accommodating. I honor the goals and requests of my clients and make it a priority to custom tailor my sessions to their specific needs. My clients describe me as genuine, warm, compassionate, knowledgeable and skilled. 

My passion for anatomy runs deep. My study of the subject includes participating in Gil Hedley’s 6-day human dissection seminars in 2005 and 2010, both of which greatly expanded and deepened my understanding of structural relationships within the human body. The whole-body, layer-by-layer integral approach of the seminars allowed me to visually and texturally comprehend how interrelated the tissues, joints and bones truly are, and profoundly changed the way I approach the structural realignment process. 

Healing is a life long journey into greater self-discovery and awareness toward wholeness. I believe strongly that we all have enormous potential to continuously change and improve our current condition. Our body's innate intelligence and interconnectedness with mind & spirit allow us to heal ourselves, if the right opportunities and circumstances are given.

Please feel free to call me at 415.359.5139 to set up an appointment!

Profile:

        Rebecca Carli became interested in somatic movement studies while pursuing B.A. and M.F.A. degrees in dance performance and choreography.  She earned certification in Rolf Movement® Integration in 1987 with Janie French and Annie Duggan.  In 1989, she became a Certified Rolfer® and in 1992, a Certified Advanced Rolfer®.   In 1994, Rebecca graduated from the Pennsylvania Gestalt Center for Psychotherapy and Training and joined the movement faculty of The Rolf Institute. 

         Rebecca?s understanding of gravity and human movement potential has been enriched by her long time studies with Hubert Godard.  Godard?s work provides the chief theoretical and practical foundation that inspires her teaching.   Additionally, she draws from her interest in the work of  Laban/Bartineff, Charlotte Selver, Julio Horvath and various forms of yoga.  Rebecca believes that embodiment is a life long process, essential for somatic practitioners. 

         Rebecca is a past Chairperson of the Rolf Movement faculty and ISMETA board representative.   Currently, she lives in the Washington D.C. area, where she maintains an active practice in Rolfing and Rolfing Movement Integration and teaches a variety of somatic movement courses.  

       Rebecca is not accepting new clients at this time.

I am passionate about helping people heal and improve their quality of life through releasing pain and tension, lengthening and balancing muscles, and aligning bones.  I am a certified Advanced Rolfer, Rolfing Movement Practitioner, and licensed Physical Therapist in the Castro neighborhood of San Francisco.  I have been practicing since 1990 (over 25 years).  I also have yoga teacher certifications.  My extensive training in these multiple disciplines and love for continued education widen the scope of techniques I have to use to heal people using the holistic Rolfing approach.  I have a keen eye for movement patterns and am skilled in assessment - keys to knowing which treatments will be most effective.  Please feel free to contact me to set up an appointment or ask specific questions and/ or see mywebsitefor more detailed information.  I look forward to helping you reach your goals.

Prior to my Rolfing training, I trained in dance, yoga and Pilates. Profile:

I have been a Rolfer(R) since 1996, a massage therapist since 1987 and completed my Advanced Rolfing training in 1996. I did my Rolfing Movement(R) certification in 2005, am an Advanced Practitioner of Biodynamic Craniosacral Therapy, have studied Neural Manipulation, Visceral Manipulation, Neurovascular Release and take frequent ceus with a manual osteopath. I am on the faculty of the University of New Mexico-Taos Structural Integration Program. Rolfing (R) Structural Integration can provide the support needed to make changes and move forward in life. It can help us to live with less pain, to stand up straight, and get in touch with our bodies. I work with an eclectic mix of people of all ages, all shapes and a wide spectrum of needs, which I find a lot of joy in. I love to help people who are ready to take the next step in their lives, whatever that may be. If you want more information, please email jillgerber4@gmail.com, or call, (505) 670-9724.
